J/A+A/553/A7        XMM sources in M83 (NGC5236)                  (Ducci+, 2013)
================================================================================
X-ray source population study of the starburst galaxy M 83 with XMM-Newton.
    Ducci L., Sasaki M., Haberl F., Pietsch and W.
   <Astron. Astrophys. 553, A7 (2013)>
   =2013A&A...553A...7D
================================================================================
ADC_Keywords: Galaxies, nearby ; X-ray sources ; Cross identifications
Keywords: galaxies: individual: M 33 - X-rays: galaxies

Abstract:
    We present the results obtained from the analysis of three XMM-Newton
    observations of M83. The aims of the paper are studying the X-ray
    source populations in M83 and calculating the X-ray luminosity
    functions of X-ray binaries for different regions of the galaxy.

    We detected 189 sources in the XMM-Newton field of view in the energy
    range of 0.2-12keV. We constrained their nature by means of spectral
    analysis, hardness ratios, studies of the X-ray variability, and
    cross-correlations with catalogues in X-ray, optical, infrared, and
    radio wavelengths.

Description:
    We analysed the public archival XMM-Newton data of M83 (PIs: Watson,
    Kuntz). Three observations were analysed, one pointing at the centre
    of the galaxy (obs.1) and two in the south, which covered the outer
    arms with a young population of stars discovered with GALEX.

