Note (1): Table 1: XMM-Newton observations of M83
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                  EPIC  EPIC   EPIC
 No  ObsID      Date         RA           DE       PN    MOS1   MOS2   Mode
                                                  F Texp F Texp F Texp PN MOS
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  1 0110910201 2003-01-27 13:37:05.16 -29:51:46.1 t 21.2 m 24.6 m 24.6 EFF FF
  2 0503230101 2008-01-16 13:37:01.09 -30:03:49.9 m 15.4 m 19.0 m 19.0 EFF FF
  3 0552080101 2008-08-16 13:36:50.87 -30:03:55.2 m 25.0 m 28.8 m 28.8 EFF FF
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 where:
  F is the filter, t for thin, m for medium, Texp is the exposure time in ks,
   and EFF = extended full frame imaging mode; FF = full frame imaging mode.
Note (2): HRi = (Ri+1 - Ri)/(Ri+1 + Ri), where
  R1 = 0.2-0.5keV
  R2 = 0.5-1keV
  R3 = 1-2keV
  R4 = 2-4.5keV
  R5 = 4.5-12keV
