Note (3): detected with
  * ROSAT (Ehle et al. 1998A&A...329...39E: [E1998]; <[EPB98] NN> in Simbad;
         Immler et al. 1999A&A...352..415I: [I1999]; <[IVE99] HNN> in Simbad),
  * Einstein (Trinchieri et al. 1985ApJ...290...96T: [T1985]; 
         <[TFP85] HN> in Simbad)
  * Chandra (Soria & Wu, 2003A&A...410...53S: [SW2003]).
Note (4): For each source the identification proposed by the respective authors
  and our classification are given. Uncertain classifications are given in
  brackets. For each counterpart, we assigned a "grade" A, B, or C if the
  positions of the X-ray source and its counterpart are closer than 1x, 2x, 3x
  combined statistical errors, respectively.
Note (5): the classes are (within brackets for uncertain classification):
    AGN = Active Galaxy Nucleus
     CV = Cataclysmic variable (binary)
    SNR = SuperNova Remnant
    SSS = Super-Soft Source
    GAL = Galaxy
    ULX = Ultra-Luminous X-ray source
    XRB = X-ray binary
     fg. star = foreground star
  hard source = hard X-ray source
